<br>
I want honest answers too.<br>
<br>
I, Recent, completed my Epic Quest.<br>
<br>
A Friend, seeing I was obviously going mad Green-Farming in najena, offered to dual quest the final page i needed (Fire)  I accepted this offer and ended the torture of that place (I wont be going back here EVER again)<br>
<br>
I dual quested the pegasus cloak with a good bard friend, in exchange for a Breath of Harmony when I come across one.<br>
<br>
I was unable to commit 3 days to a Plane of Sky Raid (Dont get me wrong, i SO would have loved to, but I was busy Saturday) and my guild got a crown for me.<br>
<br>
Now, a Question.<br>
<br>
Does this make my epic reward less worthwhile, less respectable?  I have has many people tell me no it doesnt, but a few have.<br>
<br>
Here is how I see it.<br>
<br>
Verant themselves has said they LIKE Multi-Questing, how it brings friends together to help each other and such.<br>
<br>
(Note that my Elemental Binder was also given to me by a friend, It isnt like going and grabbing one would have been hard, thats why i didnt mention it)<br>
<br>
Well...I figure my friends helping me is an &quot;Alternate&quot; Way of obtaining the items.  To some people it may seem these items come free, but they really dont.  I have spent many months building friendships, and assisting my guild.  Just as long or longer as said camp would take.  (No, i didnt help friends and my guild out JUST to get items.  Dont want people thinking that.)<br>
<br>
So...is this REALLY wrong?  <br>
<br>
Thanks for your time all.<br>
<br>
Falaanla Marr<br>
Fennin Ro<br>
