<br>
It all comes down to a matter of your own morals and play style.  Whatever anyone else says or tells you is their opinion and I would take it with a grain of salt.<br>
<br>
I just spent the last two nights on camps forgoing my RL responsibilities.  I'm starting to pay for them now and have to wonder what lies ahead for me if I ever plan on completing my epic.  The first all nighter was for Quillmane which I started after many of my guildmembers logged for the night.  After about 8 hrs and falling asleep at the keyboard, I gave up.  Mind you, I also camped Quill for about 6 hrs a few days before that, and enlisted the help of two druids and another fellow mage from my guild a few days before that too for about 6 hrs. Still no sign of Quillmane.<br>
<br>
Last night, I pulled an all-nighter with three fellow guild members (one of them also a mage) in Najena trying to get the black tome.  While we were there, we cleaned out everything else trying to get the other mage his focus items (I have all of mine) and the pages for our epics.  After 10 hours of staring at each other in that tiny room and killing Najena counteless times, still no tome, the mage managed to get the rest of his focus items and some pages with the help of a few other passing mages looking for pages/focus items but we are both without the last page, the earth page.<br>
<br>
I have a guild member who already got Quill's cloak while passing through S. Karana without camping.  I guess if I really wanted to, I could ask if they would multi quest with me but I doubt I'm going to go that route for a variety of reasons.  Personally, I'm determined to get as many of the items I can without multi questing so I can have the gratification of knowing I earned the items myself.  I know there will come times when I will have to enlist the help of friends and guild members, and I'm sure there may be times when RL will step in and prevent me from attending Plane raids or long camps, but until that time comes, I'm aiming to get as many of the items as I can so that I don't have to multi quest.<br>
<br>
I already got my elemental binder, given to me as a gift when I was a young lvl 8 mage by a passer-by at the Tunnel who said he couldn't see me walking around without any protection on my head <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  At the time I thought it was a wonderful gift, but didn't know the true value behind it. It wasn't until about two months ago that I found out I needed it for my epic.  When I get to the level of going to The Hole, I'll most likely go there and try to get the crown with another mage who needs the binder to help them out, and to say I can do it.  <br>
